Polymetal Falls to Seven-Month Low as Silver Extends Drop

-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 
2011-05-12T14:56:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/polymetal-falls-to-seven-month-low-as-silver-extends-decline.html
OAO Polymetal, the Russian precious-
metals producer, fell to its lowest price since October as
silver and gold dropped.  The shares slid 4.9 percent to 457 rubles at the 6:45 p.m.
close in Moscow, the lowest closing price since Oct. 1.  Silver for immediate delivery retreated 5.3 percent to
$33.6375 per ounce, and gold for immediate delivery fell 0.5
percent to $1,492.70 per ounce.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jack Jordan in  London  at 
 jjordan22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Kirkland in London at 
 skirkland@bloomberg.net . 